cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with personalized product search and re-ranking of search results based on user preferences. It also involves the use of implicit feedback to model user preferences, which is a common technique in IR research. 

The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as word embeddings and context-aware models, which are commonly studied in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. 

The use of machine learning models to capture long-term and short-term context dependencies also falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories are less likely but still possible as the paper involves the use of deep learning models and neural networks, which are commonly used in these fields.
